Prompt 3 – Backend REST API Endpoints (Full List)

```
Implement the following REST API endpoints in Django REST Framework. Use class‑based views or viewsets with proper serializers. Add permissions: only managers can see their team, HR sees all, employees see their own data.

### Authentication
- POST /api/login/ (returns role & user info)
- POST /api/logout/

### Engineering Manager View
- GET /api/manager/dashboard/ → summary: team members count, AI drafts ready, avg time per appraisal.
- GET /api/manager/team/ → list of employees under this manager, with appraisal completeness percentage.
- GET /api/manager/employee/<int:pk>/ → aggregated metrics (Jira, Git, feedback, self‑assessment) + AI generated draft appraisal.
- PUT /api/manager/appraisal/<int:pk>/ → update final_text, override AI, change status to approved.

### Employee View
- GET /api/employee/dashboard/ → performance trend (current score vs team benchmark), alerts (e.g., April dip).
- GET /api/employee/metrics/ → all Jira, Git, feedback, learning activities with last sync timestamps.
- POST /api/employee/context/ → add context note to a specific metric (e.g., “April low commits due to on‑call”).
- GET /api/employee/achievements/ → list of self‑submitted achievements.
- POST /api/employee/achievements/ → create new achievement.
- POST /api/employee/artifacts/ → upload supporting file (PDF/image).
- GET /api/employee/suggestions/ → AI‑powered improvement suggestions.

### HR Calibration View
- GET /api/hr/calibration/dashboard/ → cycle progress, completion rate, flagged issues.
- GET /api/hr/issues/ → list of calibration issues with AI recommendations.
- POST /api/hr/issues/<int:pk>/resolve/ → mark issue resolved, log action.
- GET /api/hr/manager-consistency/ → table of managers with avg rating, std dev, outliers count.
- GET /api/hr/audit-log/ → log of AI recommendations and manager overrides (role‑based).

Write explicit serializers and ensure all endpoints return JSON that matches the UI mockups provided in the original requirement.
```

